Nov 9, 2021 ASSOCIATED PRESS

The Labor Department reported Tuesday that its producer price index ‚Äî which measures inflation before it hits consumers ‚Äî rose 0.6% last month from September, pushed higher by surging gasoline prices. Excluding volatile food and energy prices, wholesale inflation was up 0.4% in October from September and 6.8% from a year ago.

More than 60% of the September-October increase in overall producer prices was caused by a 1.2% increase in the price of wholesale goods as opposed to services. A 6.7% jump in wholesale gasoline prices helped drive goods prices up.

Mostly dormant for decades, inflation has returned to the United States this year. The economy‚Äôs strong rebound from the 2020 coronavirus caught many businesses by surprise.
